<subsection xml:id="subsec-vector-and-scalar-quantities" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Vector and Scalar Quantities</title>
    <activity xml:id="auto_zmr1nsk3">
        <introduction xml:id="auto_iw4m6vdu">
            <p xml:id="auto_jleyj6hi">
                <alert>Work in groups</alert>
            </p>
        </introduction>
        <task xml:id="auto_dqy18otz">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_igsfo1sg">
                    Identify and list at least five examples of quantities that have both magnitude and direction.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task xml:id="auto_lhzqlhjg">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_om38vhbl">
                    Identify and list at least five examples of quantities that have only magnitude.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task xml:id="auto_0fxsae6q">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_6gv9082u">
                    Discuss how these quantities are used in real life scenarios.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task xml:id="auto_namg5y8s">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_f3s945to">
                    Discuss and share your findings with the rest of the class.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
    </activity>
    <p xml:id="auto_frm0rz6m">
        <m>\textbf{ Key Takeaway } </m>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_chlpn3w3">
        <alert>A vector</alert> is a quantity that has <alert>both</alert> 
        magnitude and direction, whereas <alert>a scalar</alert> is a quantity
        which has <alert>only</alert> magnitude.
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_jvopgj9n">
        Examples of <alert>vector</alert> quantities include force, 
        velocity, and displacement, while <alert>scalar</alert> 
        quantities include mass,temperature, and speed etc.
    </p>
    <table xml:id="auto_37ecuw1r">
        <title>Difference Between Vector and Scalar Quantities</title>
        <tabular bottom="minor" top="minor" right="minor" left="minor">
            <row header="yes">
                <cell>Feature</cell>
                <cell>Vector Quantity</cell>
                <cell>Scalar Quantity</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell>Definition</cell>
                <cell>Has both magnitude and direction</cell>
                <cell>Has only magnitude</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell>Examples</cell>
                <cell>Force,Acceleration,Displacement</cell>
                <cell>Distance,Temperature,Mass</cell>
            </row>
        </tabular>
    </table>
    
